{"cursor":"5965","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name = Destruction image = Wacken 2007 Destruction by Caroline Lauder LOUDER\n| IMAGES 258.jpg caption = Destruction at the Wacken Festival in 2007\n| image_size = background = group_or_band alias = origin = Weil am Rhein,\n| Germany genre = Thrash metal, speed metal, black metal years_active =\n| 1982–present label = Steamhammer, Nuclear Blast, AFM associated_acts =\n| website = current_members = Schmier Mike Sifringer Vaaver (Wawrzyniec\n| Dramowicz) past_members = Thomas Rosenmerkel Harry Wilkens Michael\n| \"Ano\" Piranio Christian Engler Tommy Sandmann Oliver \"Olly\"\n| Kaiser Sven Vormann Marc Reign\n}}\n\n'Destruction' is a German thrash metal band. They are considered one of the\n\"three kings\" of the Teutonic thrash metal scene, the others being\nKreator,and Sodom. All three of these bands are often credited with helping\npioneer death metal, by containing several elements of what was to become the\ngenre. Destruction were originally named Knight of Demon but changed their\nname in 1984.\n\nFor most of the 1990s, Destruction were not signed to a major record label and\nwas forced to self-produce their albums, until they signed a contract with\nNuclear Blast in the 2000s.\n","linknr":224,"url":"Destruction_(band)","recorded":1363396834,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Destruction_(band)&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Destruction_(band)&action=edit","//en.wikipedia.org/apple-touch-icon.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.wikihiero%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits